post_text:
This is the official Facebook page for RSU 22 School Board, serving the towns of Hampden, Newburgh, Winterport, and Frankfort, Maine. Please visit our website to find out more about our school district www.rsu22.us.

This page is to keep the communities of RSU 22 informed of School Board meetings, workshops, initiatives, and other activities. This is for distributing information and commenting on posts is not active. If you would like to contact the RSU 22 School Board you are encouraged to leave a private message. Please understand that messages are not regularly monitored and there may be a delay in receiving a response. If you have specific concerns, please contact the Superintendent’s Office at (207) 862-3255.

Visitors to this page are expected to follow Facebook’s Terms of Use (as applicable), as well as all applicable RSU 22 policies and procedures, copies of which are available on RSU 22’s website.

post_text:
Dear RSU 22 Families,

In the lead up to the reopening of schools for 2020, it is time to make concrete plans. RSU 22 asks you to fill out a separate survey at the link below for each one of your school age children. The survey responses will give us specific numbers and critical information to plan for re-opening. It is essential that we hear from everyone so that our plans are made based on real student numbers. Please share with your RSU 22 friends so that all families are represented. Find our survey at https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfsIYTz699EHRczvhpUjM4M-MQ4wg5YgYHuMurGmGHw3UPF7A/viewform?usp=sf_link.

Survey responses are preferred by Friday July 31st. Thank you for your participation this week.

Sincerely,

Regan Nickels

Superintendent, RSU 22

This is a friendly reminder that the RSU #22 Budget Validation Referendum will be held tomorrow, Tuesday July 14th. Voting will be open from 8:00 a.m. to 8:00 p.m. at your town's polling place:

Hampden - Skehan Recreation Center
Newburgh - Town Office
Winterport - Samuel L. Wagner Middle School
Frankfort - Congregational Church
We encourage all citizens to vote on the school budget as outlined in the most recent edition of the LINK 22 newspaper and on our district website. Please visit the Budget Information tab available at http://www.rsu22.us to view specific budget details. We thank you in advance for your participation in the budget approval process.

post_text:
Final RSU 22 school meal deliveries will be arriving tomorrow morning, Wednesday June 10th. Households will receive 5 days of meals. Summer meal pick up service will begin on Monday June 15th at Leroy Smith School in Winterport with a pickup time from 11am-noon. Meal pickup will be on Mondays for 3 days of meals and Thursdays for 4 days of meals. Parents or guardians must pick up the meals per regulations.

Check the school nutrition website under resources on the RSU 22 website for further information. https://www.rsu22.us/resources/school_nutrition

Thank you and have a safe summer!

Here is a message from Assistant Superintendent Nickels. This was also sent to parents as an e-mail.

Good morning from RSU 22,

This morning meal deliveries will occur throughout the district. Once again due to the weather being warm, we want to inform families that dairy and meat items will require refrigeration. You can expect our final meal deliveries of the school year on Friday June 5th and Wednesday June 10th. On Monday June 15th, Leroy Smith School will open as our summer meal pick up site. More details will come.

Just a reminder that online Parent Focus Groups will be hosted next week to share perspectives about your family's remote learning experiences.

The schedule is as follows and we hope you can join in:

Tuesday June 2nd Elementary PreK-5 6:00-7:00 p.m. meet.google.com/mfg-kbpn-mwp

Wednesday June 3rd Hampden Academy 7:00-8:00 p.m. meet.google.com/kgt-nnmq-izn

Enjoy the upcoming weekend,

Regan

Samuel L. Wagner Middle School
May 6 at 8:44 AM ·

Over the past couple of weeks we have been able to celebrate Administrative Professionals Day, School Lunch Hero Day, Teacher and Staff Appreciation Week (this week), and today we start National Nurses Week. It has been nice to have something positive to focus on!

In honor of National Nurses Week, we at Wagner Middle School would like to honor and thank our school nurse, Mrs. Norris. She is always a friendly, warm, and welcoming presence in our school. She helps take care of ALL of us. Thank you, Mrs. Norris! We appreciate you!

It's THOUGHTFUL THURSDAY! Because it's okay to be mad but not okay to be mean, work with your family to write down a list of all your favorite ways to calm down when you're feeling mad. Share them under this post and let others know what works for you!

Stay warm, stay happy, and stay well! ☘️

#KeepMakingArt — CREATIVE GENERATION

Hampden Academy Broncos
March 24 at 9:52 AM ·

Even now... especially now! #keepmakingart

In response to these rapid changes and worldwide uncertainty, a global movement has begun to spark joy, inspire action, and bring togetherness - #KeepMarkingArt. Please join in the art movement to bring us closer to one another and express ourselves through art making during this time of change and reflection. Students, parents, artists, teachers, everyone join in and create together - to learn more visit https://creative-generation.org/keepmakingart #KeepMakingArt is happening March 24-April 10

https://creative-generation.org/keepmakingart

DOCS.GOOGLE.COM
Chromebook Request Form

George B. Weatherbee School
March 23 at 11:34 AM ·

Dear parents,
We want to thank you for all of your support and patience. Now that our school closure has extended, our teachers are preparing to move to a digital learning platform. Weatherbee's goal is to utilize Google Classroom so we can provide a more interactive experience during the COVID school closure. We also recognize that each of you is doing the very best that you can. Lessons will be recorded so that your family can access content at a time that works best for you.

If you need a device for your student, please complete the form below. We want to ensure all students have equal access so please only request if you do not have a device. Your request will be processed quickly and we will set up a safe pick-up for you this week.

https://forms.gle/uKuAQTza9kYcsn6X7

Sincerely,
Mrs. Cyr

post_text: It is with great pleasure that the RSU #22 Board of Directors announces that Christine Boone has been unanimously confirmed this evening as our Assistant Superintendent of District Development. Christine, better known as Tina, will return to RSU 22 after three years of serving as Superintendent in Glenburn School Department. Tina previously served RSU 22 as Weatherbee School Principal and as district GT Director. She currently resides in Frankfort. Tina's official start date will be July 1, 2020.

post_text: After the election on Tuesday, 5 November, the RSU 22 School Board has 2 new directors, Tania Jean-Jacques and Faye Anderson, and one returning director, Jayne Dyer. All three are representing Hampden. Tania Jean-Jacques and Jayne Dyer will be serving three-year terms. Faye Anderson will be serving a two-year unexpired term. The Board congratulates all three directors and welcomes Tania and Faye to the RSU 22 School Board.

post_text:
The Hampden Academy Fall sports season begins tomorrow and we have an update on our HA turf field project. The turf is impressive in both appearance and safety improvements. However, have been working with our turf vendor to meet the contractual standards for the new field, and following our walkthrough today, we aren't there just yet. We will be awaiting delivery of more infill to achieve the safety and fiber protection levels we require. The infill delivery date will be forthcoming this week. For now, our teams will move ahead with tryouts on the practice field areas they have been using throughout the summer.

Can't wait to get our athletes on the turf field! Go Broncos!
text:
The Hampden Academy Fall sports season begins tomorrow and we have an update on our HA turf field project. The turf is impressive in both appearance and safety improvements. However, have been working with our turf vendor to meet the contractual standards for the new field, and following our walkthrough today, we aren't there just yet. We will be awaiting delivery of more infill to achieve the safety and fiber protection levels we require. The infill delivery date will be forthcoming this week. For now, our teams will move ahead with tryouts on the practice field areas they have been using throughout the summer.

Can't wait to get our athletes on the turf field! Go Broncos!
